  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to identify dominant geometric parameters; results are summarized in the UQ narrative. Uncertainty quantification was performed via Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition variability and material property scatter, confirming that predicted RH values remain below 1.0 across the 95th-percentile uncertainty band.",
